Purchase options and add-ons

  • Purifies your water, Perfects your skin: BWDM shower filter provide your shower with ideal water for softer and cleaner skin and hair.
  • Vitamin C 15stage Filtragtion : Quickly,naturally eliminate all the yuck in city water, hard water and well water systems.The Vitamin C nourishes skin with natural moisturizers and minimizes skin dryness. Formulated to maintain a body natural PH. Works well with hot and cold water.
  • Full compatibility: Our universal shower filters can be placed on wall-mounted, handheld, rainfall and combo shower heads for versatile home use.Universal Replacement cartridge Standard Size 2.7x 2.4 in, replacement time depending on water quality and frequency of use.Just open the housing of the shower cartridge filter, take out old and replace with new one and make sure that washer is in the slot which is inside the filter to avoid leaking.
  • Consistent water pressure: Bwdm high-performance inline water filter won't reduce existing water pressure for an improved rinse.But if you have a lot of sediments, you may need to backwash often to avoid a decrease in water flow.
  • Tool-free installation and Universal compatibility- The Bwdm ABS filter shower attaches to any inch pipe in less than 1 minute! To remove any carbon dust build-up, allow water to run through the filter for 5-10 minutes before use. Enjoy purer water!

Product Description


In the box:

1. Packing box

2. Shower Head Filter

3. Multi-layer filter

4. Teflon tape

5. Waterproof pad

6. Instruction manual

Weve thought of everything Our water softener can give you some surprises.

Heres what makes them special:

1. Please let water run through the filter for 5-10 minutes before use to remove any carbon dust build up.

2. Because of cleaner, more pure water.

3. The filter is great for well water since it removes excess heavy metals.

4. This filter is also a good choice for those who don't need a whole house water filtration system but still want to have the shower water filtered.

Easy Installation:

STEP 1: Place Rubber O-Rings

Place two rubber o-rings on both the female and male fitings of the shower filter.

STEP 2: Flush Shower Filter

Flush shwoer filer to fush out carbon powder in the activated carbon of the cartridge.

STEP 3: Install With Teflon Tape

Wrap teflon tape tightly around the threads of your shower filter and shwer arm.

STEP 4: Twist On Shower Head

Twist on shower filter and shwer head, then turn clock-wise to tighten by hand.

Filter element Silver Oil-Rubbed Bronze Brushed Nickel Filtered Shower Head 2-in-1 Enhanced Formula Multi-Stage Shower Filter

      2. AQUAYOUTH
        While your shower may look clean, it may contain potentially harmful contaminants that it picked up on its journey through aging pipes. On top of that, chlorine is added to the public water supply in order to kill bacteria and other pathogens. Chlorine and these contaminants have been linked to dry hair, dry skin, skin irritation, asthma, and more.       How customer reviews and ratings work

      Customer Reviews, including Product Star Ratings help customers to learn more about the product and decide whether it is the right product for them.

      To calculate the overall star rating and percentage breakdown by star, we dont use a simple average. Instead, our system considers things like how recent a review is and if the reviewer bought the item on Amazon. It also analyzed reviews to verify trustworthiness.

      Schlitty
      5.0 out of 5 stars A Game Changer
      Reviewed in the United States on April 25, 2023
      Style: Standard FormulaColor: ChromeVerified Purchase
      A distinctly noticeable difference in water quality at an affordable price. With some caveats.

      I don't have overly sensitive skin but I do have some allergies and the water where I live is plenty hard. Sometimes a hot shower can end up an itchy situation. While I would love a robust whole house water filtration system, it isn't practical for my situation at the moment. So I do what I can. I filter my drinking water with a pitcher. I have an individual filter on my bidet. The shower was next up. It made an instant difference that could be very clearly felt! And has continued to be felt each shower since installation. It absolutely, beyond a shadow of a doubt, made a complete difference in the feel of my shower.

      There were a couple strings attached to this though. The price can't be beat because it is indeed cheap materials. You could easily over tighten the fitting on the shower head end. I work with my hands and DIY plenty and could "feel" and hear the plastic and coating wanting to give as I secured the shower head tight. The top end, the pressure is on the wall pipe you're fitting it to. The filter compartment is thick and robust with a good design (which should make filter replacing a breeze). But where you attach the shower head, all the pressure is on the cheap material of this product. So do not use too much elbow grease. Slow, steady and even tightening until there are no leaks. That's the one objective flaw here that may or may not separate it from the more expensive choices. But, that comes with the territory of getting the cheapest option in a product category. It's all good, just something to be aware of.

      The other string is subjective. I'm tall. My shower head being another ~4 inches lower just wasn't going to work for me. So I ended up having to buy a "s-shaped shower head riser" pipe too. Which is a more involved install process. And at that point I figured I may as well upgrade my shower head too. So my cheap shower head filter turned in to a pricier full shower makeover. I'm still happy with the money I saved choosing this filter versus the more expensive options on Amazon. But I did end up spending more than I initially planned in total. If you're shorter or your shower is already higher this won't be an issue, but just throwing it out there that you may need to buy more parts if adding a ~4 inch filter to your shower head changes things too much.

      I'm a happy camper either way! My skin feels completely different now during and after a shower. I'm sure I'll become complacent and "used to" it all over time. Without a doubt a clear difference though. Highly recommend if you have hard water, sensitive skin, allergies, or just want a fresher feeling shower.
